prefix: You are an expert in number theory. Solve the following problem.
problem_prompt: You are an expert in number theory. Solve the following problem. What is the remainder when $2001 \cdot 2002 \cdot 2003 \cdot 2004 \cdot 2005$ is divided by 19?
solution: Reducing each factor modulo 19 first, we see that $2001 \cdot 2002 \cdot 2003 \cdot 2004 \cdot 2005 \equiv 6 \cdot 7 \cdot 8 \cdot 9 \cdot 10 \equiv 30240 \equiv \boxed{11} \pmod{19}$.
gpt_response:
We can find the remainder when each of the numbers is divided by 19 and then multiply the remainders together to find the remainder when the product is divided by 19.

$2001 \equiv 1 \pmod{19}$
$2002 \equiv 2 \pmod{19}$
$2003 \equiv 3 \pmod{19}$
$2004 \equiv 4 \pmod{19}$
$2005 \equiv 5 \pmod{19}$

Multiplying these remainders together gives $1 \cdot 2 \cdot 3 \cdot 4 \cdot 5 \equiv 120 \equiv 6 \pmod{19}$.

Therefore, the remainder when $2001 \cdot 2002 \cdot 2003 \cdot 2004 \cdot 2005$ is divided by 19 is $\boxed{6}$.
